Minister of Health Yuli Yoel Edelstein approved, following consultations with the Ministry of Health s professionals, a pilot for shortening the isolation period from 14 to 12 days. This pilot will continue until December 31, 2020. A person who is being isolated due to exposure to a confirmed patient or due to returning from abroad may complete his or her isolation period within 12 days, provided that the following conditions are met:
- Registering as a person in isolation in the Ministry of Health's registry, either by the online form and through Call Habriut Hotline; 
taking a first PCR coronavirus test as soon as possible after going into isolation; 
- Taking a second PCR coronavirus test 10 days after the date of the last contact with a confirmed patient or entry to Israel, and at least 24 hours after the first test; 
- Should both tests return negative, the person in isolation will receive approval either by text message or by phone call, and he or she may go out of isolation 12 days after the last date of contact with the confirmed patient or returning from abroad reported November 1, 2020.

On the 21st of February, 2021. The government of Israel has restricted sporting and cultural events to take place: Event spectators will remain seated, with no dancing and no eating in the venue; Ushers will remind spectators of the aforementioned; In case of crowd insubordination to these guidelines, the owner or the operator will stop the event. The venue's owner or operator will make sure that spectators are seated in marked seats and that tickets to the event are sold ahead of time, either online or over the phone. 
In an outdoor venue which does not include permanently fastened seats 
The venue's owner or operator will divide the venue into separate areas of up to 20 people at most, and maintain a distance of at least 2 meters between areas;
Seating will be in marked and reserved seats;
The venue's owner or operator will separate areas by physical visual cues between them; 
When seating people who do not live in the same house, a distance of two meters will be maintained between them inasmuch as possible, or at the very least an empty seat; The distance between the crowd and the stage or the place where the event is set to take place will be no fewer than four meters; The venue's owner or operator will place ushers to remind and alert event spectators that they must follow the provisions of these regulations, including the masking requirement; The number of ushers will be at a ratio of one usher per 50 spectators;

