On the 14th of June, 2020. The government of Israel has permitted the reopening event halls and gardens according to the following guidelines:

Management:
Appointment of a coronavirus supervisor for each event, responsible for ensuring compliance with the rules;
Registration of guests at the event entrance; and
The hall must be able to contact, if necessary, each guest at the event by text message, should it emerge that a COVID-19 patient was present. Contact with guests, should it be required, will be in accordance with the Ministry of Health guidelines.
Facility Guidelines:
The hall's management will place marking and signage in accordance with the Ministry of Health's guidelines, including the matter of maintaining distance of 2 meters, marking the distance at the entrance to the gathering to prevent crowding, and more;
Prior to the event and throughout the duration, internal surfaces will be disinfected frequently;
The restrooms will be cleaned and disinfected frequently, no less than once an hour; and
Stands with disinfectants will be placed in the compound, especially at the entrance and adjacent to the restrooms.
Guidelines for Guests and Employees:
The limit of people at the event at any given moment shall be one guest per 2 meters squared, provided that the number of guests in the halls which can accommodate more than 200 guests may not exceed 85% of what is allowed under the business license. This does not include operational and parking areas;
